X-WR-CALNAME:Weaver line disruption
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-03-14T23:30:00&endDate=2026-03-15T01:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nWEAVER LINE: Saturday 14 March\, after 23:15\, no service between Liverpool Street and Cheshunt / Chingford / Enfield Town. Use VICTORIA LINE connections between Central London and Seven Sisters / Walthamstow Central. Replacement buses operate.
DTEND:20260315T012900Z
DTSTART:20260314T233000Z
SUMMARY:Weaver line: Planned Closure
UID:d9139c1c-e12b-40ce-98d4-e9f40dbbf2e4@d913.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-03-17T22:45:00&endDate=2026-03-18T01:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nWEAVER LINE: Monday 16\, Tuesday 17\, Wednesday 18 and Thursday 19 March\, after 2245 each evening\, no service between Hackney Downs and Enfield Town / Cheshunt. Last through trains operate at 2245 from Liverpool Street to Cheshunt (except on Wednesday when it is at 2215)\, 2253 from Enfield Town to Liverpool Street\, 2300 from Liverpool Street to Enfield Town and 2302 from Cheshunt to Liverpool Street. Use Clapton for Rectory Road and Stoke Newington\, and local London Buses services for Stamford Hill. Replacement buses operate. The limited number of southbound GREATER ANGLIA and STANSTED EXPRESS trains after midnight which usually call at Seven Sisters are diverted via Tottenham Hale instead
DTEND:20260318T012900Z
DTSTART:20260317T224500Z
SUMMARY:Weaver line: Part Closure
UID:98d9d5ac-e062-4f0e-93e1-186d53cf3604@98d9.org
END:VEVENT
